Because if you do--

00:28:30.670 --> 00:28:31.500 align:middle line:84%
>>EMERY: Then they'll
kill you after.

00:28:31.500 --> 00:28:31.620 align:middle line:90%
It's definite, yeah.

00:28:31.620 --> 00:28:33.078 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: Yeah,
that's what he said,

00:28:33.078 --> 00:28:35.280 align:middle line:84%
then they'll kill you
and take it again.

00:28:35.280 --> 00:28:37.550 align:middle line:90%
Just don't ever build one.

00:28:37.550 --> 00:28:42.140 align:middle line:84%
And he said, I don't know
what's going to happen next.

00:28:42.140 --> 00:28:43.090 align:middle line:90%
>>EMERY: Right.

00:28:43.090 --> 00:28:45.722 align:middle line:90%
Where did the molds go?

00:28:45.722 --> 00:28:47.150 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: They never came back.

00:28:47.150 --> 00:28:48.320 align:middle line:90%
>>EMERY: Ah, that's right.

00:28:48.320 --> 00:28:49.120 align:middle line:90%
They wouldn't.

00:28:49.120 --> 00:28:50.162 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: They kept them--

00:28:50.162 --> 00:28:51.245 align:middle line:90%
>>EMERY: That makes sense.

00:28:51.245 --> 00:28:52.140 align:middle line:90%
We'd do the same.

00:28:52.140 --> 00:28:52.520 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: --at casting.

00:28:52.520 --> 00:28:53.320 align:middle line:90%
>>EMERY: Yes.

00:28:53.320 --> 00:28:55.010 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: So everything's gone.

00:28:55.010 --> 00:28:56.820 align:middle line:84%
And see, there's
another vital part

00:28:56.820 --> 00:28:58.670 align:middle line:90%
that I skipped in the story.

00:28:58.670 --> 00:29:01.650 align:middle line:84%
My dad smoked a
pipe all the time,

00:29:01.650 --> 00:29:03.290 align:middle line:90%
and he and I would sit and talk.

00:29:03.290 --> 00:29:04.740 align:middle line:90%
And he felt bad for me.

00:29:04.740 --> 00:29:08.220 align:middle line:10%
He says, you know,
you're just a kid.

00:29:08.220 --> 00:29:11.127 align:middle line:10%
And this whole thing going
on with the Air Force,

00:29:11.127 --> 00:29:12.960 align:middle line:10%
you building this rocket,
he said, you know,

00:29:12.960 --> 00:29:14.835 align:middle line:10%
things are going to get
out of hand probably.

00:29:14.835 --> 00:29:15.990 align:middle line:90%
I said, yeah.

00:29:15.990 --> 00:29:19.940 align:middle line:84%
If they do and I ever
talk to you and I'm gone

00:29:19.940 --> 00:29:22.080 align:middle line:84%
and I call back and
I say, everything's

00:29:22.080 --> 00:29:25.110 align:middle line:84%
fine, just light your
pipe and take it easy,

00:29:25.110 --> 00:29:28.560 align:middle line:84%
if I tell you to light
your pipe, go into the lab,

00:29:28.560 --> 00:29:30.820 align:middle line:84%
pull everything out, all the
drawings, all the books--

00:29:30.820 --> 00:29:31.620 align:middle line:90%
>>EMERY: Right.

00:29:31.620 --> 00:29:33.245 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: --everything,
burn everything.

00:29:33.245 --> 00:29:34.380 align:middle line:90%
Burn the models.

00:29:34.380 --> 00:29:36.308 align:middle line:90%
Burn everything.

00:29:36.308 --> 00:29:38.100 align:middle line:84%
Leave the building
where it is because it's

00:29:38.100 --> 00:29:42.270 align:middle line:84%
kind of a cool facility,
but burn everything else.

00:29:42.270 --> 00:29:48.950 align:middle line:10%
So when I was at
Area 51, Groom Lake,

00:29:48.950 --> 00:29:50.270 align:middle line:10%
they showed up at our house.

00:29:50.270 --> 00:29:50.585 align:middle line:90%
>>EMERY: Ah

00:29:50.585 --> 00:29:53.090 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: And all they found
was this real irate drunk man

00:29:53.090 --> 00:29:55.760 align:middle line:84%
in the back with a lot
of smoke and ashes.

00:29:55.760 --> 00:29:58.800 align:middle line:84%
And they were pissed,
but they left.

00:29:58.800 --> 00:30:01.800 align:middle line:84%
And LeMay said, you done
destroyed your prototype,

00:30:01.800 --> 00:30:04.860 align:middle line:90%
you wiped out the lab.

00:30:04.860 --> 00:30:08.250 align:middle line:84%
He said he would do his part
and wipe out paper trails,

00:30:08.250 --> 00:30:10.350 align:middle line:84%
and it's going to make it
very difficult for them.

00:30:10.350 --> 00:30:12.580 align:middle line:90%
It's only going to be you left.

00:30:12.580 --> 00:30:14.610 align:middle line:90%
So I went back--

00:30:14.610 --> 00:30:16.750 align:middle line:84%
let's see-- back to
Wright-Patterson.

00:30:16.750 --> 00:30:20.010 align:middle line:84%
Car took me all the way back
to my home in Mount Liberty.

00:30:20.010 --> 00:30:22.360 align:middle line:84%
And I went to school
that fall, and that's

00:30:22.360 --> 00:30:25.270 align:middle line:84%
how I spent my summer vacation
as a junior, my high school

00:30:25.270 --> 00:30:27.190 align:middle line:90%
year.

00:30:27.190 --> 00:30:28.360 align:middle line:90%
The fall was quiet.

00:30:28.360 --> 00:30:29.380 align:middle line:90%
Winter was quiet.

00:30:29.380 --> 00:30:31.390 align:middle line:90%
Spring, I graduated.

00:30:31.390 --> 00:30:34.840 align:middle line:84%
I'm in graduation line shaking
hands with the parents,

00:30:34.840 --> 00:30:39.090 align:middle line:84%
I'm in a cap and gown, I got a
full scholarship to Ohio State

00:30:39.090 --> 00:30:41.590 align:middle line:90%
in theoretical astrophysics.

00:30:41.590 --> 00:30:44.180 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to be a professor,
teach the rest of my life,

00:30:44.180 --> 00:30:45.126 align:middle line:90%
keel over, that's it.

00:30:45.126 --> 00:30:45.492 align:middle line:90%
>>EMERY: Right.

00:30:45.492 --> 00:30:47.450 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: So I'm shaking
hands with the parents.

00:30:47.450 --> 00:30:48.770 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, I'm going to--

00:30:48.770 --> 00:30:54.060 align:middle line:84%
and I grab this hand over
here and it's ice cold.

00:30:54.060 --> 00:30:57.640 align:middle line:84%
I turn around and it's
two guys in black suits,

00:30:57.640 --> 00:31:01.420 align:middle line:84%
white shirts, little skinny
ties, mirror sunglasses.

00:31:01.420 --> 00:31:04.510 align:middle line:84%
What is it with these guys
and that attire, you know?

00:31:04.510 --> 00:31:07.240 align:middle line:90%
And he hands me this letter.

00:31:07.240 --> 00:31:12.380 align:middle line:84%
And I open it up and it
says, greetings, I'm drafted.

00:31:12.380 --> 00:31:13.590 align:middle line:90%
It's June 10, 1972.

00:31:13.590 --> 00:31:14.430 align:middle line:84%
>>EMERY: They're
making you join.

00:31:14.430 --> 00:31:15.230 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Yeah.

00:31:15.230 --> 00:31:17.320 align:middle line:90%
>>EMERY: The war's almost over.

00:31:17.320 --> 00:31:19.400 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: The draft didn't
shut down until 1975.

00:31:19.400 --> 00:31:20.200 align:middle line:90%
>>EMERY: Right.

00:31:20.200 --> 00:31:23.440 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: This is June 10,
1972, and they grab me.

00:31:23.440 --> 00:31:24.430 align:middle line:90%
I'm in cap and gown.

00:31:24.430 --> 00:31:27.340 align:middle line:84%
They drag me across
the parking lot.

00:31:27.340 --> 00:31:30.825 align:middle line:84%
And all the kids are
wondering what's going on.

00:31:30.825 --> 00:31:31.625 align:middle line:90%
>>EMERY: Right.

00:31:31.625 --> 00:31:33.422 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: And on my
DVD, they actually

00:31:33.422 --> 00:31:34.880 align:middle line:84%
find these kids
and interview them.

00:31:34.880 --> 00:31:37.130 align:middle line:84%
They said, yeah, we don't
know what happened that day.

00:31:37.130 --> 00:31:39.960 align:middle line:84%
They drug him off, threw
him in a blue station wagon,

00:31:39.960 --> 00:31:40.802 align:middle line:90%
and he was gone.

00:31:40.802 --> 00:31:42.510 align:middle line:84%
>>EMERY: So there was
a lot of witnesses.

00:31:42.510 --> 00:31:43.310 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Yeah.

00:31:43.310 --> 00:31:46.110 align:middle line:84%
And they said, we heard him
yell to his parents something

00:31:46.110 --> 00:31:49.290 align:middle line:90%
about legal conscription.

00:31:49.290 --> 00:31:52.930 align:middle line:84%
It means that they can
physically take you legally.

00:31:52.930 --> 00:31:53.840 align:middle line:90%
So they did.

00:31:53.840 --> 00:31:58.450 align:middle line:84%
And a couple hours later, we're
at Port Columbus in Columbus,

00:31:58.450 --> 00:31:59.820 align:middle line:90%
Ohio at the airport.

00:31:59.820 --> 00:32:03.360 align:middle line:84%
We go down to the end to
MAT, Military Air Transport,

00:32:03.360 --> 00:32:06.180 align:middle line:84%
and there's Rudolph
waiting with a jet.

00:32:06.180 --> 00:32:07.170 align:middle line:90%
>>EMERY: Mm-mm.

00:32:07.170 --> 00:32:09.000 align:middle line:84%
This is the first time you've
seen him since the incident.

00:32:09.000 --> 00:32:09.360 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Since then.

00:32:09.360 --> 00:32:09.820 align:middle line:90%
>>EMERY: Oh, no.

00:32:09.820 --> 00:32:11.278 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: That's
who's orchestrating

00:32:11.278 --> 00:32:13.570 align:middle line:90%
the whole damn thing.

00:32:13.570 --> 00:32:17.750 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know there's this
internal civil war going on.

00:32:17.750 --> 00:32:18.550 align:middle line:90%
>>EMERY: Right.

00:32:18.550 --> 00:32:20.680 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: I get out
of the station wagon.

00:32:20.680 --> 00:32:22.630 align:middle line:10%
Rudolph and his guys
come out, and they

00:32:22.630 --> 00:32:27.070 align:middle line:10%
pull their MPK5s and
whatever, and they're

00:32:27.070 --> 00:32:28.840 align:middle line:10%
looking big and bad.

00:32:28.840 --> 00:32:33.160 align:middle line:84%
And then another truck pulls
up behind our station wagon.

00:32:33.160 --> 00:32:36.830 align:middle line:10%
All these Air Force guys jump
out, got all theses M16s.

00:32:36.830 --> 00:32:38.320 align:middle line:90%
They all cock and load.

00:32:38.320 --> 00:32:41.140 align:middle line:84%
Now they're pointing
guns at each other.

00:32:41.140 --> 00:32:42.190 align:middle line:90%
>>EMERY: Oh, no.

00:32:42.190 --> 00:32:43.210 align:middle line:90%
This is a huge contest--

00:32:43.210 --> 00:32:44.480 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: Yeah, and
I'm going, oh, God.

00:32:44.480 --> 00:32:45.605 align:middle line:90%
>>EMERY: --of who gets you.

00:32:45.605 --> 00:32:46.680 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Who gets me?

00:32:46.680 --> 00:32:48.138 align:middle line:84%
I'm standing there
in between them.

00:32:48.138 --> 00:32:50.620 align:middle line:84%
I thought, I should just
start a firefight right here,

00:32:50.620 --> 00:32:53.200 align:middle line:84%
die in the middle of it,
and be the end of it.

00:32:53.200 --> 00:32:55.060 align:middle line:84%
But I was looking at
all these young guys,

00:32:55.060 --> 00:32:57.250 align:middle line:84%
and I could see they
wanted to go home.

00:32:57.250 --> 00:32:59.260 align:middle line:10%
So I walked over
to Colonel Williams

00:32:59.260 --> 00:33:02.940 align:middle line:10%
and said, let me go
with him, Rudolph,

00:33:02.940 --> 00:33:05.750 align:middle line:10%
and let all your guys go home.

00:33:05.750 --> 00:33:07.473 align:middle line:10%
I'll deal with this.

00:33:07.473 --> 00:33:08.390 align:middle line:10%
Williams looked at me.

00:33:08.390 --> 00:33:09.310 align:middle line:10%
He said, you sure?

00:33:09.310 --> 00:33:11.335 align:middle line:10%
Yeah, just let me go.

00:33:11.335 --> 00:33:12.623 align:middle line:90%
>>EMERY: That's very brave.

00:33:12.623 --> 00:33:15.290 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: Well, I didn't want any
of these people to get shot up.

00:33:15.290 --> 00:33:17.680 align:middle line:90%
So I got on board with Rudolph.

00:33:17.680 --> 00:33:19.280 align:middle line:90%
We take off.

00:33:19.280 --> 00:33:26.080 align:middle line:84%
And a few hours later, there we
are, Langley, home of the CIA.

00:33:26.080 --> 00:33:29.930 align:middle line:90%
And then Rudolph starts in.

00:33:29.930 --> 00:33:34.865 align:middle line:10%
I'm put in this room that
looks like a hospital room--

00:33:34.865 --> 00:33:35.665 align:middle line:10%
>>EMERY: Hm.

00:33:35.665 --> 00:33:38.980 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: --with a bed and the
oxygen things and all that.

00:33:38.980 --> 00:33:41.830 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, well,
this doesn't look good.

00:33:41.830 --> 00:33:44.500 align:middle line:10%
They wheel in this big stainless
steel table, and I'm going,

00:33:44.500 --> 00:33:46.570 align:middle line:10%
oh, brother.

00:33:46.570 --> 00:33:49.470 align:middle line:84%
So I grab a chair and
commence going at it,

00:33:49.470 --> 00:33:51.550 align:middle line:90%
and I'm overpowered.

00:33:51.550 --> 00:33:55.442 align:middle line:10%
Rudolph comes in next with
his friends in lab coats.

00:33:55.442 --> 00:33:56.620 align:middle line:90%
I'm stripped naked.

00:33:56.620 --> 00:33:59.750 align:middle line:90%
I'm tied to this table.

00:33:59.750 --> 00:34:00.890 align:middle line:90%
Rudolph looked at me.

00:34:00.890 --> 00:34:03.600 align:middle line:84%
He said, been waiting
to see you again.

00:34:03.600 --> 00:34:05.600 align:middle line:84%
And he throws this
cloth on this table

00:34:05.600 --> 00:34:08.969 align:middle line:84%
and it was all these
needles and little vials.

00:34:08.969 --> 00:34:11.630 align:middle line:84%
And I'm looking, trying
to read the bottles.

00:34:11.630 --> 00:34:14.913 align:middle line:84%
And I'm seeing sodium
pentothal, sodium barbital,

00:34:14.913 --> 00:34:15.830 align:middle line:90%
all the sodium family.

00:34:15.830 --> 00:34:17.430 align:middle line:90%
>>EMERY: Truth-telling serums.

00:34:17.430 --> 00:34:18.230 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Yeah.

00:34:18.230 --> 00:34:21.710 align:middle line:84%
Man, they stick it in in this
hand, right on that vein,

00:34:21.710 --> 00:34:23.840 align:middle line:90%
and it feels like liquid fire.

00:34:23.840 --> 00:34:25.550 align:middle line:84%
And it got up to
right about my neck,

00:34:25.550 --> 00:34:26.842 align:middle line:90%
and that's the last I remember.

00:34:26.842 --> 00:34:29.190 align:middle line:90%


00:34:29.190 --> 00:34:31.190 align:middle line:84%
You're only supposed to
be under for 30 minutes.

00:34:31.190 --> 00:34:32.630 align:middle line:84%
>>EMERY: They mind
swept you, yeah.

00:34:32.630 --> 00:34:33.430 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Yeah.

00:34:33.430 --> 00:34:35.830 align:middle line:90%
30 minutes is the limit.

00:34:35.830 --> 00:34:39.909 align:middle line:84%
They went at me for three
days, day and night.

00:34:39.909 --> 00:34:44.960 align:middle line:84%
And I came around somewhere
a day and a half into it.

00:34:44.960 --> 00:34:47.335 align:middle line:84%
And I was laying there, and
I can remember one guy saying

00:34:47.335 --> 00:34:50.595 align:middle line:84%
to Rudolph, if you do him again,
he's going to be an eggplant,

00:34:50.595 --> 00:34:51.395 align:middle line:90%
you know.

00:34:51.395 --> 00:34:52.953 align:middle line:90%
And Rudolph said, I don't care.

00:34:52.953 --> 00:34:54.370 align:middle line:84%
>>EMERY: You'll
be all gorked out.

00:34:54.370 --> 00:34:55.170 align:middle line:90%
>>ADAIR: Yeah.

00:34:55.170 --> 00:35:01.240 align:middle line:84%
I need to know the info out of
the construction of this fusion

00:35:01.240 --> 00:35:02.710 align:middle line:90%
device.

00:35:02.710 --> 00:35:07.560 align:middle line:84%
So he was sitting in
there by whoever, CIA

00:35:07.560 --> 00:35:11.940 align:middle line:84%
probably, still after
the first strike device,

00:35:11.940 --> 00:35:14.090 align:middle line:90%
and they can't get it.

00:35:14.090 --> 00:35:18.070 align:middle line:84%
So I finally come back
to and I'm laying there.

00:35:18.070 --> 00:35:21.190 align:middle line:84%
You ever come out from under
this stuff, it's amazing.

00:35:21.190 --> 00:35:23.710 align:middle line:84%
You can talk and
answer questions,

00:35:23.710 --> 00:35:25.108 align:middle line:90%
but you're not there.

00:35:25.108 --> 00:35:26.900 align:middle line:84%
Lights are on, but
there ain't nobody home.

00:35:26.900 --> 00:35:27.900 align:middle line:90%
>>EMERY: No one's there.

00:35:27.900 --> 00:35:31.720 align:middle line:10%
>>ADAIR: So I finally
focused into where

00:35:31.720 --> 00:35:33.480 align:middle line:10%
everybody's in the room.

00:35:33.480 --> 00:35:34.980 align:middle line:84%
And the guy is
asking me a question.

00:35:34.980 --> 00:35:40.490 align:middle line:84%
He said, how do you
feel about missiles?

00:35:40.490 --> 00:35:43.950 align:middle line:84%
I ain't building any
more, I can tell you that.

00:35:43.950 --> 00:35:45.957 align:middle line:84%
And so he comes back,
goes outside the room.

00:35:45.957 --> 00:35:47.040 align:middle line:90%
You hear people out there.

00:35:47.040 --> 00:35:48.393 align:middle line:90%
He comes back in.

00:35:48.393 --> 00:35:49.810 align:middle line:84%
How do you feel
about jet engines?

00:35:49.810 --> 00:35:51.980 align:middle line:90%
I went, they're defensive.

00:35:51.980 --> 00:35:53.800 align:middle line:90%
I could work on that.

00:35:53.800 --> 00:35:57.010 align:middle line:84%
So they tell me, you're
not going to Camp Lejeune.

00:35:57.010 --> 00:35:59.170 align:middle line:84%
You're going to Great
Lakes, Illinois.

00:35:59.170 --> 00:36:00.140 align:middle line:90%
You're in the Navy.

00:36:00.140 --> 00:36:01.000 align:middle line:90%
>>EMERY: Oh, my.

00:36:01.000 --> 00:36:02.500 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: And they
get through there,

00:36:02.500 --> 00:36:05.290 align:middle line:84%
and then they send me to
Pensacola, the Naval training

00:36:05.290 --> 00:36:05.545 align:middle line:90%
schools.

00:36:05.545 --> 00:36:06.345 align:middle line:90%
>>EMERY: Sure.

00:36:06.345 --> 00:36:09.610 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: Well, I graduated
first in my class,

00:36:09.610 --> 00:36:14.622 align:middle line:90%
and they sent me to Norfolk.

00:36:14.622 --> 00:36:15.795 align:middle line:90%
>>EMERY: Good old Norfolk.

00:36:15.795 --> 00:36:17.520 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: They were
stuck on something.

00:36:17.520 --> 00:36:22.800 align:middle line:90%
This is 1972, '73.

00:36:22.800 --> 00:36:25.560 align:middle line:84%
And you know what Norfolk
was at that moment?

00:36:25.560 --> 00:36:27.590 align:middle line:90%
Detroit of the F-14.

00:36:27.590 --> 00:36:28.570 align:middle line:90%
>>EMERY: Really?

00:36:28.570 --> 00:36:29.400 align:middle line:84%
>>ADAIR: That's
where it was built.

00:36:29.400 --> 00:36:30.317 align:middle line:90%
>>EMERY: That's right.

00:36:30.317 --> 00:36:32.550 align:middle line:10%
>>ADAIR: So I'm sitting
there, and they told me,

00:36:32.550 --> 00:36:35.880 align:middle line:10%
we've got 5,000
engineers stymied

00:36:35.880 --> 00:36:38.160 align:middle line:10%
on the turbines of the F-14.

00:36:38.160 --> 00:36:45.180 align:middle line:84%
They cannot find to get a ratio,
you know, one to 15, one to 16.

00:36:45.180 --> 00:36:51.180 align:middle line:10%
The power needed, this is going
to be a fighter bomber, first

00:36:51.180 --> 00:36:52.570 align:middle line:10%
of its kind.

00:36:52.570 --> 00:36:54.910 align:middle line:10%
So I looked at it.

00:36:54.910 --> 00:36:56.120 align:middle line:10%
I said, what's your problem?

00:36:56.120 --> 00:37:00.290 align:middle line:10%
